<!--
  Plan-then-apply change-set preview — reference shape for `anvil:memo`.

  This template documents the canonical shape of a `plan.md` artifact
  produced by `memo-revise <thread> --plan` (and optionally
  `memo-revise <thread> --polish "<reason>" --plan` when composing with
  the polish-pass flag). The plan is a critic-sibling-shaped artifact
  that lives at `<thread>.{N+1}.plan/plan.md` — i.e., the same
  versioned-suffix convention as `<thread>.{N+1}.review/` and
  `<thread>.{N+1}.audit/`, NOT inside a version dir. The plan sibling
  does NOT contain `memo.md` — that file is written by the subsequent
  `memo-revise --apply` invocation, which produces the actual
  `<thread>.{N+1}/` version dir.

  See `commands/memo-revise.md` §"Plan-then-apply mode (`--plan` /
  `--apply`)" for the writer-side contract, and `SKILL.md`
  §"Operator-confirmable change-set preview" for the user-facing shape.

  OPERATOR USE:
  The operator EDITS this file in place to reject or modify planned
  items before invoking `memo-revise <thread> --apply`. Three accepted
  rejection shapes — pick whichever fits the editor flow:

  1. Comment out the row with `<!-- declined: <reason> -->` on the same
     line as the table row. The reason is required.
  2. Delete the row entirely. Resulting changelog row reads
     `Resolution: declined — removed from plan` with no operator-supplied
     reason.
  3. Replace the `Priority` cell value with `declined` and add a
     bracketed reason at end of `Summary` (e.g., `[declined: out of
     scope for this pass]`).

  Declined items become `Resolution: declined — <reason>` rows in
  `<thread>.{N+1}/changelog.md` after `--apply` runs.
-->

